Murfreesboro.Collier-Lane-Crichlow House: The Collier-Lane-Crichlow House is a historic house in Murfreesboro, Tennessee, U.S.. It was built circa 1850 for architect Sterling P. Jones, who designed in the Federal, Georgian and Greek Revival architectural styles. It was purchased by brothers Jessie A. Collier and Newton C. Collier in 1858.
